latestPosts.caption:
From flow to mama mode, this is what my practice looks like these days. A little strength, a lot of softness, and always, always love.

Yoga has shifted since becoming a mama… it’s less about pushing and more about presence. Less perfection, more play.

Whether it’s 5 minutes or 25, this flow grounds me and reminds me: I can be both, strong and gentle.

Save this if you need a moment of calm in your day.

Tell me! What does your version of self-care look like right now? I’d love to hear.

Ever wondered why Korean skin always looks so effortlessly healthy & not just glowy on the surface, but actually strong and calm underneath?

It’s because they don’t just chase glow they protect their skin barrier first.
And that’s exactly why Aestura is a game-changer. This brand is the #1 dermatologist-recommended in Korea and it’s finally here in India!

I’ve been trying their Atobarrier range (you’ll see why it’s gone viral globally) —
with tiny ceramide capsules that strengthen your barrier, lock in hydration for 120 hours, and leave your skin feeling like it’s had a reset.

Exclusively available on @mynykaa ❤️

#AD #Aestura #KBeauty #BarrierCare #GlowFromWithin

7 months of Rumi. 🧿 Swipe to see how much fun she had. 

She’s already a beach baby; happiest near the ocean, falling asleep to the sound of the waves in our arms.

These are the little moments I know I’ll miss someday.

Also… the secret to surviving summer heat with a baby? Linen everything! This dreamy dress from @akashi.clothing made chasing (and cuddling) a 7-month-old look a lot more effortless than it felt.

Drop your favorite baby summer memories below: I love reading them!

#LifeLately #MotherhoodUnplugged #BeachDayVibes #SummerWithBaby

latestPosts.caption:
Adulting is a scam and life is hard, so tell me:

What’s your secret life hack that feels like cheating at life but is actually just brilliant?

No gatekeeping allowed — I want the weird, the random, and the life-changing! 

Whenever I don’t feel doing something, I tell myself that the future me would be so pleased with me when she find out that she doesn’t have to do it, and it has helped me so much! Also I always tell myself that I’ll only do something for 5 minutes and then most of the time I end up completing the task. 

Dropping mine first. Now your turn — I’m ready to steal your genius ideas!
